Step 1: Identify the Accounts Receivable balances from the balance sheet.  
• Initial Accounts Receivable = 0.00  
• Ending Accounts Receivable = 200359.99  

Step 2: Calculate the Average Accounts Receivable by taking the average of the beginning and ending balances.  
 Average Accounts Receivable = (0.00 + 200359.99) / 2 = 100179.995  

Step 3: Identify the Revenue from the income statement.  
• Main Business Revenue = 547392.30  

Step 4: Use the formula for the Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio:  
 Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio = Revenue / Average Accounts Receivable  
 = 547392.30 / 100179.995  
 ≈ 5.47  

Thus, the Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio is approximately 5.47.
